      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Skipping your basal dose of insulin is not recommended, even if you had a light dinner. Insulin helps to regulate blood sugar levels around the clock, not just after meals. You should take your regular dose as prescribed to prevent hypoglycemia. If you're concerned about your blood sugar dropping too low, you might want to consume a small carbohydrate snack, drink some juice, or eat a slice of toast to help stabilize your levels. Always be sure to monitor your blood sugar closely and consult your healthcare provider if you're unsure.",
