    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's understandable to be concerned about a potential low blood sugar hit, but skipping your basal insulin dose can be risky. Insulin works continuously to manage your blood sugar levels and skipping it can lead to a dangerous drop. Since your doctor is strict, you might want to consider other options like eating a small snack or drinking a sugary beverage to help raise your blood sugar. If you're worried about crashing, setting a reminder to call your doctor first thing in the morning could help. In the meantime, monitor your blood sugar closely and be prepared to act if you notice any symptoms of hypoglycemia. Remember, it's better to err on the side of caution with your medication.",
      "source": "target",
